class Solution:
    def checkOnesSegment(self, s: str) -> bool:
        return "01" not in s


"""
Approach & Reasoning:

Since the string has no leading zeros and starts with '1',
all 1s form at most one contiguous segment exactly when
we never see a transition from '0' back to '1'.

The pattern "01" means:
- a block of 1s ended,
- and later another 1 appears.

So:
- if "01" exists, there are at least two segments of 1s → return False
- otherwise, all 1s are in one contiguous segment → return True

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
"""
